	The Financing of Terrorism in Northern Ireland
</major-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/westminhall/2003-05-01.143.2" nospeaker="true" colnum="143"  time="unknown" url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmhansrd/vo030501/halltext/30501h01.htm#30501h01_head0">
	<p class="italic">[Relevant documents: Fourth Report from the Northern Ireland Affairs Committee, Session 2001&ndash;02, HC 978-I, and the Government's response thereto, Sixth Special Report, Session 2001&ndash;02, HC 1347.]</p>
	<p class="italic">Motion made, and Question proposed, That the sitting be now adjourned.&mdash;[Derek Twigg.]</p>
</speech>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/westminhall/2003-05-01.144.0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1103" speakername="Michael Mates" colnum="144"  time="14:30:00" url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmhansrd/vo030501/halltext/30501h01.htm#30501h01_spnew0">
	<p>I am happy to agree to this adjournment in the special circumstances that we are needed elsewhere. I shall raise a point of order in the Chamber after questions to try to ensure that we have a system that does not put us all in the position of having to adjourn a debate that could more easily be postponed until the important statement is over. In the circumstances, I am happy to agree with the Government's motion.</p>
	<p class="italic">Question put and agreed to.</p>
	<p class="indent">Adjourned accordingly at half-past Two o'clock.</p>
</speech>
